                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer text-sm">
                    Is ABSI useful if my BMI is already normal?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Yes. One of the motivations for ABSI was that some people
                    with a “normal” BMI still carry a lot of fat around the
                    abdomen, which is more strongly linked to cardiometabolic
                    risk. A high ABSI with normal BMI can flag this pattern of
                    central obesity.
                  </p>
